y)</span><hr size=1> I had a big long post with an idea all laid out but of course i forgot to copy it before submit and of course IE nuked it.  So you get the short version<br>
<br>
<br>
Teer's Reduction in Tears Plan (tm)<br>
<br>
<br>
When rage pops the first force that is ready to ENGAGE calls for a random.  If their is no others ready then that force engages. If there is 2 or more forces then they do a random and set up an order.  The winning force then engages at that moment, not in 5 min but right there.  If they wipe then it goes to the 2nd force in the random list.  If 2 groups show up and don't have the right numbers to kill, they can join together but only get one spot for random.  There is no second try if you wipe (unless other forces ok it obviously).  <br>
<br>
I had a bunch of explanation and this and that but it got nuked and I am at work so no time to explain more.  Take this idea for what its worth.  There WILL be more KSes, claim morals/repect but the bottomline is that the more it happens the less it will be respected and it WILL spiral down from there into other areas of guild relationships.<br>
<br>
This basically keeps clerics from having to waste 5 days of their life and their friends only to lose in what they think is a KS.  While you won't have the perceived guarantee of a rage for a 5 day camp, it does eliminate the need for a 5 day camp so that people won;t feel so darn hurt over a stupid game.<br>
<br>
Rage is on a timer so you know about when he will pop.  People are more than welcome to wait there and it will probably give them more time to mobilize if that is a problem for you.<br>
<br>
